      • UserAccount

        public UserAccount()
        Required for serialization. Do not use directly.

      • UserAccount

        public UserAccount​(String username,
                   String password,
                   String role)
        Constructor for UserAccount class. Creation of this object does not save the user into the database.
        Parameters:
        username - Unique identifier for the user.
        password - User password (may not be hashed depending on the context).
        role - GrantedAuthority compatible string identifier for user ACL access rights.

      • UserAccount

        public UserAccount​(NewUserDTO userDTO)
            throws Exception
        Constructor for UserAccount class. Utilizes the NewUserDTO to ensure that protected fields such as ROLE are not exposed in the controller.
        Parameters:
        userDTO - DTO object from frontend Model.
        Throws:
        Exception - Given password pair does not match.
        See Also:
        NewUserDTO
